{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce the electronic tourist authorisation to 90 days",
        "additional_details": "Some countries only allow tourists to enter for a maximum of 90 days without a visa\r\n \r\nWe think the current UK tourist visa waiver of up to 6 months is completely unnecessary and totally out of line with the way some other countries deal with tourists\r\n \r\nMany countries have a standard waiver at 90 days, and few allow tourists longer stays without first applying for a visa\r\n \r\nAt a time when controlling borders is so important, we think allowing huge numbers of people to enter the country without a visa is totally unacceptable\r\n \r\nWe think we should align with other countries and limit visa free entry to 90 days maximum",
        "background": "The United Kingdom has offered visa free entry for up to 6 months for citizens of certain countries since 1947\r\n \r\nWe think this is completely out of line with the way other countries deal with tourist access",
